Table 5.   Justice system employment and percent distribution of full-time equivalent employment,
by State and level of government, October 1995
Notes:  Local government data are estimates subject to variability.
This spreadsheet has been corrected since it was first released in the CJEE, 1995.
a/ Total full-time equivalent employment includes employment of States and all types of local governments including
independent school districts and special districts, which are not displayed separately.  The "Local, total" lines, which
include these districts, will not equal the sum of the "Counties" and "Municipalities" lines.
b/ Justice system employment of independent school districts and special school districts (primarily for special police)
